										<string>// Create a new text style object based on the style of the "Main Text" layer at the first character and first line.&#xD;var newStyle = thisComp.layer("Master Text").text.sourceText.getStyleAt(0,0);  &#xD;&#xD;// Check if the current time is before the start of the composition (negative time).&#xD;// If it is, set the newText to "Ég" as a placeholder. This part might be for initialization purposes.&#xD;// If the time is 0 or positive, split the text from "Processed Text" at every line break ("\r"), &#xD;// and attempt to take the third segment (which is the third line), trim any whitespace from the ends,&#xD;// and then use this as the newText. If the third segment does not exist, use an empty string.&#xD;var newText = (time &lt; 0) ? "Ég" : thisComp.layer("Processed Text").text.sourceText.split("\r")[2]?.trim() || "";&#xD;&#xD;// Apply the newText to the newStyle, which will change the text while keeping the original style.&#xD;newStyle.setText(newText);&#xD;</string>
